news.title: NCLT orders restart of Lavasa insolvency process after resolution plan failure
news.para: The Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT), while directing the revival process to be re-initiated, also directed the Committee of Creditors (CoC) to exclude the period from July 13, 2021, to January 3, 2022, from the resolution process.

news.title: RBI imposes penalties on Godrej Housing, HUDCO and Aadhar Housing Finance
news.para: As per the official statement from RBI on Friday, it has imposed a monetary penalty of Rs 5 lakh on Godrej Housing Finance Limited, Rs 5 lakh on Aadhar Housing Finance Limited, and Rs 3.5 lakh on Housing and Urban Development Corporation Limited.

news.title: Noida authority seals Grand Omaxe society over Rs 457 crore dues
news.para: The developer failed to deposit the mandated 25% of recalculated dues, around Rs 114.4 crore, after the Covid zero-period reduction, upfront even after opting in for the relief package.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance raises Rs 1,758 crore from anchor investors
news.para: Investment Trust Plc, SBI Life Insurance Company, ICICI Prudential Life Insurance Company, HDFC Mutual Fund (MF), Kotak Mahindra MF, SBI MF, UTI MF and Nippon India MF are among the anchor investors.

news.title: Deloitte India leases 81,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai’s Goregaon
news.para: Deloitte India has leased nearly 81,000 sq ft of office space in Mumbai's Goregaon for over five years. The lease includes a rental escalation clause and a significant security deposit. This move follows another major lease in Delhi's Aerocity, reflecting Deloitte's growth plans in India.

news.title: Greater Noida authority auctions three plots for Rs 521 crore
news.para: The biggest of these plots was secured by Eldeco Infrastructure and Properties Ltd, while Prasu Infrabuild and Divyansh Infraheight jointly secured the second plot. Purvanchal Projects emerged the winning bidder for the third and smallest of the three plots.

news.title: Indonesia's Waskita, banks agree on $2.05 billion debt restructuring
news.para: The restructuring terms for most of those loans include lowering interest rates payable on the loans to 3.5% per annum from 5% and extending their maturities to 2032, Muhammad said.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises raises Rs 1,500 crore by selling shares through QIP
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Friday, Brigade Enterprises said a committee of directors approved the allotment of 1,30,43,478 equity shares to eligible qualified institutional buyers.

news.title: House prices in UK rise 4.3% in August 2024: Halifax
news.para: House prices increased by 4.3% in August, the biggest annual gain since November 2022 - shortly after the economic agenda of former Prime Minister Liz Truss triggered a financial crisis and a spike in mortgage rates.

news.title: SC grants bail to Bhushan Steel's former promoter in PMLA case
news.para: Singal has appealed against the January 8 order of the Delhi High Court by which his bail plea and petition challenging his arrest by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) in the case were dismissed.

news.title: Unfinished infrastructure projects cause difficulties for Ahmedabad residents
news.para: The Rs 104 crore flyover at Pallav Junction in Naranpura, the Vadaj crematorium development project, the Vastrapur lake development project, the Sola Science City road development project, and the Chandlodia multi-level parking project are among those that have missed their deadlines, causing difficulties for the public.

news.title: Mumbai, Delhi are least affordable for residential investment in 2024: Magicbricks
news.para: Based on the P/I Ratio, Magicbricks said that Chennai (5), Ahmedabad (5), and Kolkata (5) are among the most affordable cities for residential investments in 2024, while the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (14.3) and Delhi (10.1) emerged as the least affordable.

news.title: Gujarat government introduces new rules to cut TP process by five months
news.para: The urban development department (UDD) has made several modifications to speed up the drafting and finalization of TP schemes after thorough deliberation. The govt will establish an Original Plot Approval Committee (OPAC) to ensure the integrity of the original plot's boundary and area until the preliminary scheme receives approval.

news.title: Industrialists of Pimpri Chinchwad object to conversion of industrial to residential plots
news.para: Members of the organisation of industrialists from the twin cities claim such conversion is allowing developers to build residential structures in industrial areas, which is ultimately affecting both residents and industry members

news.title: Delhi development body to hand over flat documents in 'customised' folders
news.para: The LG found the lack of papers - their non-availability, being disputed, having got lost, etc. as one of the prime woes afflicting various individuals, groups and processes of DDA. He had accordingly directed DDA to prepare a folder containing not only the possession letter but all relevant documents to be handed over to the buyers, the statement read.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC stays construction of colony in Narmada corridor in Jabalpur
news.para: The municipal commissioner and SDM in charge of the area had ordered the demolition of houses in the illegal colony in the past, but for two years, there has been no action for the removal of the colony.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC orders FIR against two builders for land fraud in Jabalpur
news.para: The bench of Justice Vishal Dhagat said that the probe report by Omti division CSP, which was handed over to SP Jabalpur, and the public prosecutor, both state that prima facie, a case is made out against the two builders— Adarsh Agarwal and Sushil Nigam.

news.title: Delhi HC stays Rs 111-crore demand by L&DO on ITC Maurya land
news.para: Justice Sanjeev Narula, while issuing notice to the L&DO of the Urban Development Ministry, also stayed the two demand notices of March 14 and April 22 asking ITC to pay ground rent of ₹111.06 crore. The matter has been kept for further hearing on October 22.

news.title: Ghaziabad: NGT directs hotels, restaurants & malls to get pollution certificate in three months
news.para: NGT asked the UPPCB to take "punitive, preventive, prohibitive and remedial steps including, assessment and recovery of environmental compensation, expeditiously " against establishments that were previously granted time by it to obtain consent to operate certificate but had not done so.
